Doctor Whisper Drew is a zoologist who has learned how to speak the languages of all wild animals, along with making him one of the top men in his field this skill proves very helpful at the zoo where he keeps his offices.

Along with being a world ranging expert in animals Dr. Drew also from time to time finds himself called on to solve crimes. In this endeavor he is aided by Zan the Jungle Boy, Mikko the monkey and occasionally one of the dogs that found and raised Zan in Africa.

deck: Resident of Buckaroo, Oregon. She's the daughter of Sheriff Shannon Crane and the Nailbiter.
description:
Origin

The relationship between high school sweethearts Shannon Crane and Edward Warren ended when Edward left Shannon a note saying he was afraid to hurt her (Edward would later become the serial killer known as the Nailbiter). But Shannon was already pregnant by him and she decided to keep the baby.

Putting her daughter Alice up for adoption in Portland, Shannon discovered that no one wanted a baby from Buckaroo, Oregon, the town that spawned several serial killers. Alice was taken in a foster home in Buckaroo.

Alice grew up curious about the serial killers of Buckaroo, Oregon. She investigated the connection between all Buckaroo Butchers, partly because she was afraid to become one herself.
